udience. The most important authors and texts of the period are categorized not according to genre, but rather chronologically, each being described within its culture-historical context and accompanied by useful bibliographical references. The book also briefly discusses some general questions about this undeservedly little-known literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aByzantine literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aByzanz / Literatur, Kulturgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aByzantine Studies (literature, cultural history).08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2007z9783110277135oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2007z9783110277005oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311018878340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091231940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110912319423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110912319/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2007  aZDB-23-DGGb2007  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014